body_html:
@caisq any ideas why our Docker instance's installed TF would have a separate set of symbols than the pip installed ones?

I indeed verified as well that the pip installed package does contain the missing symbol @aleist needs, but don't know why the Docker version would be different.

$ nm _pywrap_tensorflow_internal.so | grep _ZN10tensorflow10ReaderBase4ReadEPNS_14QueueInterfaceEPSsS3_PNS_15OpKernelContextE
00000000028e5280 T _ZN10tensorflow10ReaderBase4ReadEPNS_14QueueInterfaceEPSsS3_PNS_15OpKernelContextE
